<subSubSection pageId="162" pageNumber="163" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="162" pageNumber="163">
151b. 
<taxonomicName LSID="ED238070-1FC7-57D9-8429-B8C91EF4EC97" authority="(Boiss.) J. R. I. Wood &amp; R. W. Scotland" authorityName="J. R. I. Wood &amp; R. W. Scotland" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="Wood &amp; Williams &amp; Mitchell &amp; Carine &amp; Harris &amp; Scotland" baseAuthorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus calvertii subsp. ruprechtii" order="Solanales" pageId="162" pageNumber="163" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="calvertii" status="stat. nov." subSpecies="ruprechtii">Convolvulus calvertii subsp. ruprechtii (Boiss.) J.R.I.Wood &amp; R.W.Scotland</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="162" pageNumber="163">stat. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="162" pageNumber="163" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="162" pageNumber="163">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wood &amp; Williams &amp; Mitchell &amp; Carine &amp; Harris &amp; Scotland" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="J. R. I. Wood &amp; R. W. Scotland" baseAuthorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus ruprechtii" order="Solanales" pageId="162" pageNumber="163" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ruprechtii" status="stat. nov.">Convolvulus ruprechtii</taxonomicName>
Boiss., Fl. Orient. [Boissier] 4: 96. 1875. (
<bibRefCitation author="Boissier, E" editor="Boissier, E" journalOrPublisher="H. Georg, Geneva, Basle and Lyons" pageId="199" pageNumber="200" pagination="84 - 123" refId="B46" refString="Boissier, E, 1875b. Convolvulaceae. In: Boissier, E, Ed., Flora Orientalis 4: Corolliflorae and Monochlamydeae. H. Georg, Geneva, Basle and Lyons: 84 - 123" title="Convolvulaceae." volumeTitle="Flora Orientalis 4: Corolliflorae and Monochlamydeae." year="1875 b">Boissier 1875b</bibRefCitation>
: 96). Type. RUSSIA, Daghestan, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="162" pageNumber="163">Ruprecht</emphasis>
s.n. (lectotype G 00330221!, specimen from &quot;Daghestania prope Kutuschi,&quot; designated here; isolectotypes G!, LE).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="162" pageNumber="163" type="type">
<paragraph pageId="162" pageNumber="163">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="162" pageNumber="163">
Based on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wood &amp; Williams &amp; Mitchell &amp; Carine &amp; Harris &amp; Scotland" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="J. R. I. Wood &amp; R. W. Scotland" baseAuthorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus ruprechtii" order="Solanales" pageId="162" pageNumber="163" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ruprechtii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="162" pageNumber="163">Convolvulus ruprechtii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Boiss.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="163" pageNumber="164" type="distinguishing features">
<paragraph pageId="163" pageNumber="164">
<pageBreakToken pageId="163" pageNumber="164" start="start">Distinguishing</pageBreakToken>
features.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="163" pageNumber="164">
Leaves and stem silvery with appressed sericeous hairs; spreading hairs absent or almost so. Leaves broadly oblong to obovate, up to three times as long as broad. 
<bibRefCitation author="Petrov, VA" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe de Naturalistes de Moscou, Section Biologique" pageId="208" pageNumber="209" pagination="132 - 150" refId="B265" refString="Petrov, VA, 1935. Revisio critica specierum Convolvuli generis in viciniis florae USSR sponte nascentium. Bulletin de la Societe de Naturalistes de Moscou, Section Biologique 44: 132 - 150" title="Revisio critica specierum Convolvuli generis in viciniis florae USSR sponte nascentium." volume="44" year="1935">Petrov 1935</bibRefCitation>
: 144 (plate).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="163" pageNumber="164" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="163" pageNumber="164">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="163" pageNumber="164">
Crimea (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">Vasak</emphasis>
s.n. [29/7/1977]); Russia: Dagestan (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">Tsvelev et al</emphasis>
. 1020, 2850, 3164, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">Alexeenko</emphasis>
952, 9355, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">Grossheim</emphasis>
s.n. [25/6/1915]); Armenia (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">Fayvush et al.</emphasis>
04-0424); Azerbaijan (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">Grossheim et al.</emphasis>
s.n. [10/6/1947]); Iran (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">Miller et al.</emphasis>
s.n. [17/5/2005]). Principally in the eastern Caucasus around 1500 m.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="163" pageNumber="164" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="163" pageNumber="164">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="163" pageNumber="164">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boiss., Diagn. Pl. Orient., ser. 2, 3: 124. 1856. (Boissier" authorityYear="1856" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus calvertii" order="Solanales" pageId="163" pageNumber="164" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="calvertii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">Convolvulus calvertii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recognised by the near sessile flowers with bracts often overtopping the heads are distinctive. It is easily confused with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boiss., Diagn. Pl. Orient. 11: 81. 1849. (Boissier" authorityYear="1849" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus commutatus" order="Solanales" pageId="163" pageNumber="164" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="commutatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">Convolvulus commutatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boiss., Diagn. Pl. Orient. 11: 82. 1849. (Boissier" authorityYear="1849" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus schirazianus" order="Solanales" pageId="163" pageNumber="164" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="schirazianus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">Convolvulus schirazianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but is distinguished by the distinct spreading hairs on the stem. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Desr., Encycl. [Lamarck et al.] 3: 551. 1792. (Desrousseaux" authorityYear="1792" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus lanuginosus" order="Solanales" pageId="163" pageNumber="164" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lanuginosus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">Convolvulus lanuginosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in the pilose ovary and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Juz., Bot. Mater. Gerb. Bot. Inst. Komarova Akad. Nauk. S. S. S. R. 12: 219. 1950. (Juzepczuk" authorityYear="1950" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus sericocephalus" order="Solanales" pageId="163" pageNumber="164" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sericocephalus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">Convolvulus sericocephalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the sparse indumentum of the inflorescence so the sepals are easily visible.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
